	abstract = {Network-based approach is rapidly emerging as a promising strategy to integrate and interpret different -omics datasets, including metabolomics. The first section of this chapter introduces the current progresses and main concepts in multi-omics integration. The second section provides an overview of the public resources available for creation of biological networks. The third section describes three common application scenarios including subnetwork identification, network-based enrichment analysis, and systems metabolomics. The section four introduces the concept of hierarchical community network analysis. The section five discusses different tools for network visualization. The chapter ends with a future perspective on multi-omics integration.},
